[SN]TITLE[SN]
Stamp thief funded 'first-class' lifestyle with £90,000 haul

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A thief who stole £90,000 of postage stamps to fund first-class holidays and a lifestyle "beyond his means" has been jailed.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Andrew Swales, 39, pocketed thousands of first and second class stamp books while working as manager of a Co-op store, police said.
He sold them to pay for foreign trips, electrical goods and his gambling habit, Sheffield Crown Court heard.
Swales, of Thongsbridge, in Holmfirth, pleaded guilty to theft by employee.
