The court heard Swales stole the stamps from the store in Snape Hill Road, Darfield, South Yorkshire, between 2009 and 2012.
He then sold the stamps to a stamp dealer in London for 70% of their face value, pocketing about £60,000 South Yorkshire Police said.
He was arrested after an internal investigation revealed large, high-value orders of postage stamps were unaccounted for.
The court heard Swales had attempted to blame a colleague but when police raided his home a large number of first and second class stamps were recovered.
